compiler, core

### Description

Currently, the `@error` block doesn't support any options, it would be great to support two use-cases:

1. get access to the error itself to be able to parametrize the error block content
2.  to retry failed fetching of the lazy loaded component bundle file



### Proposed solution

```
@error (err; retry: 3) {  <p>Ooops {{err}}</p> }

// or even 
@error (err, retry: customRetryHandler)  {  <p>Ooops {{err}}</p> }
```

### Alternatives considered

Taping into requests with HTTP interceptor and trying to filter out failures for this lazy loading process?

